A new catechism short and plain, and very necessary to be learned of the youn ger [sic] sort, before they come to be partakers of the Holy Communion. Published for the benefit of Shaffham School, Norfolk. By Geo. Dochant, minister of Gods word, and there teacher in a private school. Dochant, George.
[8] p.
Printed, and are to be sold at the sign of the Black-spread-Eagle at the West end of Pauls, London : 1653. [i.e., 1654]
Actual publication date from Wing. Signatures: A⁴. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Feb: 21". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
